TITLE: Testing Promise Resolution Order
DESCRIPTION: Initial test implementation showing basic promise resolution order checking. Uses Jest mocks to verify that queued async calls resolve in the correct sequence.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dubzzz/fast-check/blob/main/website/docs/tutorials/detect-race-conditions/your-first-race-condition-test.mdx#2025-04-11_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
test('should resolve in call order', async () => {
  // Arrange
  const seenAnswers = [];
  const call = jest.fn().mockImplementation((v) => Promise.resolve(v));

  // Act
  const queued = queue(call);
  await Promise.all([queued(1).then((v) => seenAnswers.push(v)), queued(2).then((v) => seenAnswers.push(v))]);

  // Assert
  expect(seenAnswers).toEqual([1, 2]);
});
```

